### Deploy with Vercel CLI (bash)

Source: https://context7.com/vercel/vercel/llms.txt

Command-line snippets for deploying projects using the Vercel CLI. Dependencies: vercel CLI installed and authenticated (VERCEL_TOKEN or logged in). Inputs are CLI flags and environment variables; outputs are remote deployments and logs. Limitations: examples assume network access and correct project/environment configuration.

```bash
# Deploy current directory to production
vercel --prod

# Deploy with environment variables
vercel --env DATABASE_URL=postgres://... --env API_KEY=abc123

# Deploy specific directory with build settings
vercel ./app --build-env NODE_ENV=production --regions iad1,sfo1

# Deploy and wait for completion
vercel --prod --yes --no-wait=false

# Deploy to specific target environment
vercel --target staging

# Deploy with custom project name
vercel --name my-project

# Deploy prebuilt output directory
vercel --prebuilt

# Link local project to Vercel project
vercel link

# Pull environment variables
vercel env pull .env.local

# Run local development server
vercel dev --listen 3000

# View deployment logs
vercel logs https://my-app-abc123.vercel.app

# Inspect deployment
vercel inspect https://my-app-abc123.vercel.app
```

